  "texts": [
    "In the domain of organic fertilizers, BSF larvae frass emerges as a valuable option for sustainable cultivation globally.",
    "However, further investigation is needed regarding the potential of frass obtained from composting biodegradable wastes using BSF larvae.",
    "The composition of frass varies considerably, with nutrient concentrations like P, K, and micronutrients being heavily dependent on the feed substrate.",
    "As frass may not possess the optimal nutrient composition, particularly being P-dominated, supplementing it with another nutrient input, specifically N-dominated, could create a more balanced fertilizer.",
    "Future studies should explore nutrient supplementation for frass-based fertilizers to meet the specific needs of different crops."
  ],
